\f0 \cf2 Box Legends
\f1\fs53\fsmilli26667 \

\f0\fs32 Box 1 | Mechanistic taxonomy of the postoperative immune\'96ecological remodelling window
\f1\fs42\fsmilli21333 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf3 Postoperative Crohn\'92s disease comprises biologically distinct remodelling phenotypes characterised by differential contributions of epithelial dysfunction, immune activation and fibrotic remodelling. Recognition of barrier-dominant, immune-dominant and fibrosis-dominant PIERW phenotypes may enable mechanism-matched prevention strategies rather than uniform postoperative prophylaxis.
\f2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

