\f5\b\fs28 \cf3 Patient B | Immune-dominant PIERW
\f2\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf3 A 34-year-old man with penetrating ileocolonic Crohn\'92s disease (B3 phenotype) undergoes repeat resection following secondary loss of response to adalimumab and prior intra-abdominal abscess formation. Histopathology demonstrates marked mesenteric inflammation (\'93creeping fat\'94) with dense lymphoplasmacytic infiltration and prominent Th1/Th17 transcriptomic activation. Serological testing is positive for ASCA-IgG and anti-OmpC antibodies.
\f2\fs32 \

\f0\fs28 At postoperative week 4, CRP concentration is 28 mg L\uc0\u8315 \'b9 and faecal calprotectin exceeds 1,000 \u956 g g\u8315 \'b9. He is classified as having an immune-dominant remodelling phenotype and commences ustekinumab in combination with azathioprine. Intestinal ultrasound at 3 months shows no transmural inflammatory activity, and 6-month ileocolonoscopy demonstrates Rutgeerts i0 disease.
\f2\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

