\f5\b\fs28 \cf3 Clinical implication
\f2\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf3 These vignettes illustrate how similar surgical procedures may initiate biologically divergent postoperative trajectories. Under conventional postoperative algorithms, all three patients would typically receive similar surveillance and prophylactic strategies. Within the PIERW framework, however, postoperative management is aligned to the dominant remodelling mechanism \'97 epithelial-barrier instability, adaptive immune activation or fibrotic progression \'97 enabling mechanism-matched prevention rather than uniform prophylaxis.
\f2\fs32 \

\f0\fs28 This shift represents a conceptual transition from static postoperative risk categorisation towards dynamic biological trajectory management.
\f2\fs32 \
