\f5\b\fs28 Box 2 | Adaptive precision-prevention trial architecture during PIERW
\f2\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl520\qj\partightenfactor0

\f5\b\fs28 \cf3 Trial concept.
\f0\b0  A biomarker-stratified, response-adaptive platform trial enrolling patients immediately after ileocolonic resection, designed to evaluate integrated prevention 
\f6\i ecosystems
\f0\i0  rather than isolated therapies.
\f2\fs32 \

\f5\b\fs28 Step 1 | Baseline biological stratification.
\f0\b0  Participants are classified into barrier-dominant, immune-dominant or fibrosis-dominant phenotypes using a pre-specified multi-omics algorithm integrating: (i) anastomotic histopathology (plexitis, mast-cell density, adipocyte morphology); (ii) mucosal transcriptomics (barrier-function, Th1/Th17 and fibrotic gene modules); (iii) faecal microbiota (alpha-diversity, 
\f6\i F. prausnitzii
\f0\i0  relative abundance); (iv) faecal calprotectin and plasma CRP; and (v) AI-derived imaging signatures from resection specimens.
\f2\fs32 \

\f5\b\fs28 Step 2 | Mechanism-matched randomisation.
\f0\b0  Within each stratum, participants are randomised to mechanism-matched interventions:
\f2\fs32 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl520\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\f6\i\fs28 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Barrier-dominant
\f0\i0 : vedolizumab alone 
\f6\i versus
\f0\i0  vedolizumab plus cyclical partial enteral nutrition (or CDED).
\f2\fs32 \
\ls6\ilvl0
\f6\i\fs28 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Immune-dominant
\f0\i0 : anti-TNF 
\f6\i versus
\f0\i0  ustekinumab, with optional immunomodulator augmentation based on prior exposure.
\f2\fs32 \
\ls6\ilvl0
\f6\i\fs28 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Fibrosis-dominant
\f0\i0 : standard biologic prophylaxis 
\f6\i versus
\f0\i0  biologic plus investigational anti-fibrotic agent (e.g., TGF-\uc0\u946  pathway inhibitor).
\f2\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl520\qj\partightenfactor0

\f5\b\fs28 \cf3 Step 3 | Dynamic adaptation.
\f0\b0  Bayesian adaptive modelling continuously updates individual recurrence probability using longitudinal biomarker trajectories, intestinal ultrasound at 3 and 6 months, and AI-assisted ileocolonoscopy at 6\'9612 months. Pre-specified biomarker thresholds trigger treatment escalation (within-class dose intensification or cross-class switch) or de-escalation (biologic spacing or withdrawal in deep remission), mimicking a closed-loop control system.
\f2\fs32 \

\f5\b\fs28 Step 4 | Integrated endpoints.
\f0\b0  Co-primary endpoints span three domains: (i) 
\f6\i Biological
\f0\i0 \'97Rutgeerts score, transmural healing on intestinal ultrasound, biomarker remission (faecal calprotectin <100 \uc0\u956 g g\u8315 \'b9), and microbiome restoration; (ii) 
\f6\i Human-centred
\f0\i0 \'97EQ-5D-5L utility values, food-related quality of life, treatment burden, adherence durability, and work productivity; and (iii) 
\f6\i Systems-level
\f0\i0 \'97repeat surgery, biologic switching rate, cumulative corticosteroid exposure, and cost per remission-year.
\f2\fs32 \

\f5\b\fs28 Conceptual implication.
\f0\b0  By embedding nutritional, pharmacological and monitoring interventions within a single adaptive architecture, this design moves beyond the binary drug-versus-placebo paradigm and generates the preference-based, cost-effectiveness evidence required by health technology assessment agencies.
\f2\fs32 \
